      • toBoolean

        public static boolean toBoolean(java.lang.String str,
                                boolean defaultValue)
        Converts a string boolean to a boolean. This accepts the following values (case-insensitive, space-trimmed): 
              true, 1, on, yes ... true
      false, 0, off, no ... false
        If neither of those values is recognized, then the given default value is returned.

      • toDouble

        public static double toDouble(java.lang.String str,
                              double defaultValue)
        Convert a stringified double to a double. This catches the NumberFormatException of Double.parseDouble(java.lang.String), and returns a default value instead.
